Install NTFS-3G (recommended)

# First, enable EPEL repository
dnf install epel-release -y

# Then install ntfs-3g
dnf install ntfs-3g -y


If EPEL isn't available or you're offline, try:
dnf install ntfsprogs -y


Mount manually after installing:
mount -t ntfs-3g /dev/sdb1 /run/media/root/RHEL-10-1-B


Why this happens: RHEL 10 ships without NTFS kernel support by default due to licensing reasons. The ntfs-3g package provides NTFS support in userspace as a workaround.
If you don't have internet access, you'd need to:

Download the ntfs-3g RPM package from another machine
Transfer it via another USB drive (formatted as ext4 or FAT32)
Install with rpm -ivh ntfs-3g-*.rpm
